title: Hip Hop Declares Ronda Rousey's Career Latest Victim Of 2016
text:
Hip Hop Declares Ronda Rousey's Career Latest Victim Of 2016 December 31, 2016 | 10:27 AM 8 
Las Vegas, NV – Ronda Rousey’s return to the octagon was over in 48 seconds. The UFC fighter was knocked out in the first round by Amanda Nunes last night (December 30) at T-Mobile Arena in Las Vegas. 
This was Rousey ‘s first match in 13 months when she took a hiatus after suffering the first loss of her career, a knockout at the hands of Holly Holm in November of last year. 
Her comeback was short lived as Nunes, the defending women’s bantamweight champion, came out the gate throwing punch after punch that landed right on Rousey’s face. Referee Herb Dean called off the match less than a minute in. 
Hip Hop responded to the fight with shock and helped fuel the swirling speculation that the 29-year-old fighter will retire.
